<pre class="bz_comment_text">In regard to cron directories, yes. But I suspect they may be some other packages out there that suffer from the same thing.

Did you ever considered a mechanism, similar to the dpkg-statoverrride, that would allow packages to register particular permissions for files/directories to enforce permissions, so even if a package merges with, for example, 755, portage would force it to 750?

I think this is something that could be done even on bashrc level with post_pkg_postinst hook to adjust the on-rootfs permissions as well as do the same on pre_pkg_merge to adjust them in $D, so in case that they don't exist on rootfs, they would be merged with the globally enforced permissions.</pre>
